    "Parameter file values take precedence over environment variable values.",
    "The SUNDB cluster system has background processes (gmaster) for managing instances on each member node.",
    "The gmaster process consists of multiple system threads.",
    "System threads in gmaster include ClusterRecover Thread and Failover Thread.",
    "The ClusterRecover Thread handles the recovery of global transactions in cluster mode.",
    "The Failover Thread is responsible for failover handling when specific nodes or network failures occur.",
    "The cdispatcher process is responsible for sending/receiving cluster data packets and session management.",
    "The cserver process performs change and query operations on its member node's database.",
    "The gmon tool monitors the gmaster process.",
    "gmon can be set to auto-execute by setting GMON_AUTOSTART to 1.",
    "One gmaster can monitor only one gmon process.",
    "MEM_TRANS_TBS is used for recovering global transactions in the cluster system.",
    "The size of MEM_TRANS_TBS is automatically calculated based on the transaction table size and the number of cluster nodes.",
    "Database or instance settings can be changed by modifying the text parameter file or redefining environment variables.",
    "The gmaster process manages boot-up, log flushing, aging, and other overall database operations.",
    "The SUNDB database does not adopt a multi-threaded architecture but rather a shared memory-based multi-process architecture.",
    "The SUNDB database can be used in standalone or cluster mode.",
    "When the SUNDB instance is terminated, the gmaster management daemon also terminates.",
    "The SUNDB instance can be ended in four ways: NORMAL, TRANSACTIONAL, IMMEDIATE, and ABORT.",
